Food prices in Finland fall significantly faster than the EU average
Food prices in Finland are drastically lowering to the delight of consumers and to the annoyance of producers.
The price of food in Finland has fallen by almost five per cent in three years, while in the EU countries the price of food fell by 0.9 per cent on average.
