The word trampoline comes from the Spanish word el trampol<0xC3><0xAD>n, which means "springboard".
Ambitious masters jump on a huge trampoline, which throws them to an altitude of almost 10 meters. Before descending on their feet, jumpers must make a series of acrobatic movements, such as threads, folds and folds.
